{"id":"316023180_A_general_system_for_heuristic_minimization_of_convex_functions_over_non-convex_sets","abstract":"We describe general heuristics to approximately solve a wide variety of problems with convex objective and decision variables from a non-convex set. The heuristics, which employ convex relaxations, convex restrictions, local neighbour search methods, and the alternating direction method of multipliers, require the solution of a modest number of convex problems, and are meant to apply to general problems, without much tuning. We describe an implementation of these methods in a package called NCVX, as an extension of CVXPY, a Python package for formulating and solving convex optimization problems. We study several examples of well known non-convex problems, and show that our general purpose heuristics are effective in finding approximate solutions to a wide variety of problems.","authors":["S. Diamond","R. Takapoui","S. Boyd"],"meta":["April 2017Optimization Methods and Software 33(1):1-29","DOI:10.1080/10556788.2017.1304548"],"references":["284085730_Variations_and_extension_of_the_convex-concave_procedure","267695858_Convergence_of_alternating_direction_method_with_multipliers_for_non-convex_composite_problems","266972236_An_ADMM_Algorithm_for_Clustering_Partially_Observed_Networks","264828728_Distributed_optimal_power_flow_using_ADMM","263663231_Global_Convergence_of_Splitting_Methods_for_Nonconvex_Composite_Optimization","255907318_Nonconvex_Splitting_for_Regularized_Low-Rank_Sparse_Decomposition","255907067_A_Nonconvex_Admm_Algorithm_for_Group_Sparsity_With_Sparse_Groups","237092139_Optimal_Parameter_Selection_for_the_Alternating_Direction_Method_of_Multipliers_ADMM_Quadratic_Problems","236661594_An_Improved_Three-Weight_Message-Passing_Algorithm","236202968_Linear_Models_Based_on_Noisy_Data_and_the_Frisch_Scheme","226029783_On_the_Douglas-Rachford_splitting_method_and_the_proximal_point_algorithm_for_maximal_monotone_operators","323233579_The_Packin